{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"So for any of us in this room today,\nlet's start out by admitting we're lucky."},{"time":5365,"text":"We don't live in the world\nour mothers lived in,"},{"time":8216,"text":"our grandmothers lived in,"},{"time":9479,"text":"where career choices\nfor women were so limited."},{"time":12368,"text":"And if you're in this room today,"},{"time":14000,"text":"most of us grew up in a world\nwhere we have basic civil rights,"},{"time":18768,"text":"and amazingly, we still live in a world\nwhere some women don't have them."},{"time":23381,"text":"But all that aside,\nwe still have a problem,"},{"time":26110,"text":"and it's a real problem."},{"time":27349,"text":"And the problem is this:"},{"time":29000,"text":"Women are not making it\nto the top of any profession"},{"time":33196,"text":"anywhere in the world."},{"time":35094,"text":"The numbers tell the story quite clearly."},{"time":37551,"text":"190 heads of state --\nnine are women."},{"time":41000,"text":"Of all the people\nin parliament in the world,"},{"time":43490,"text":"13 percent are women."},{"time":45798,"text":"In the corporate sector, women at the top,"},{"time":48666,"text":"C-level jobs, board seats --"},{"time":51000,"text":"tops out at 15, 16 percent."},{"time":53765,"text":"The numbers have not moved since 2002"},{"time":56741,"text":"and are going in the wrong direction."},{"time":59212,"text":"And even in the non-profit world,"},{"time":61368,"text":"a world we sometimes think of\nas being led by more women,"},{"time":64664,"text":"women at the top: 20 percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68022,"text":"We also have another problem,"},{"time":69464,"text":"which is that women face harder choices"},{"time":71878,"text":"between professional success\nand personal fulfillment."},{"time":75475,"text":"A recent study in the U.S.\nshowed that, of married senior managers,"},{"time":80545,"text":"two-thirds of the married men had children"},{"time":83000,"text":"and only one-third\nof the married women had children."},{"time":86669,"text":"A couple of years ago, I was in New York,"},{"time":88703,"text":"and I was pitching a deal,"},{"time":90183,"text":"and I was in one of those fancy\nNew York private equity offices"},{"time":93558,"text":"you can picture."},{"time":94755,"text":"And I'm in the meeting --\nit's about a three-hour meeting --"},{"time":97589,"text":"and two hours in,\nthere needs to be that bio break,"},{"time":100772,"text":"and everyone stands up,"},{"time":102603,"text":"and the partner running the meeting\nstarts looking really embarrassed."},{"time":106261,"text":"And I realized he doesn't know\nwhere the women's room is in his office."},{"time":110558,"text":"So I start looking\naround for moving boxes,"},{"time":113125,"text":"figuring they just moved in,\nbut I don't see any."},{"time":115435,"text":"And so I said, \"Did you just\nmove into this office?\""},{"time":118760,"text":"And he said, \"No,\nwe've been here about a year.\""},{"time":121629,"text":"And I said, \"Are you telling me\nthat I am the only woman"},{"time":125754,"text":"to have pitched a deal\nin this office in a year?\""},{"time":129000,"text":"And he looked at me, and he said,"},{"time":130610,"text":"\"Yeah. Or maybe you're the only one\nwho had to go to the bathroom.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":134215,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":136638,"text":"So the question is,\nhow are we going to fix this?"},{"time":141607,"text":"How do we change these numbers at the top?"},{"time":144883,"text":"How do we make this different?"},{"time":147619,"text":"I want to start out by saying,\nI talk about this --"},{"time":150280,"text":"about keeping women in the workforce --"},{"time":153000,"text":"because I really think that's the answer."},{"time":155613,"text":"In the high-income part of our workforce,"},{"time":157899,"text":"in the people who end up at the top --"},{"time":160000,"text":"Fortune 500 CEO jobs,\nor the equivalent in other industries --"},{"time":165000,"text":"the problem, I am convinced,\nis that women are dropping out."},{"time":168671,"text":"Now people talk about this a lot,"},{"time":171000,"text":"and they talk about things\nlike flextime and mentoring"},{"time":174038,"text":"and programs companies\nshould have to train women."},{"time":176547,"text":"I want to talk about none of that today,"},{"time":178476,"text":"even though that's all really important."},{"time":180502,"text":"Today I want to focus\non what we can do as individuals."},{"time":183695,"text":"What are the messages\nwe need to tell ourselves?"},{"time":186000,"text":"What are the messages we tell\nthe women that work with and for us?"},{"time":189188,"text":"What are the messages\nwe tell our daughters?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":191641,"text":"Now, at the outset,\nI want to be very clear"},{"time":194064,"text":"that this speech comes with no judgments."},{"time":196170,"text":"I don't have the right answer."},{"time":197774,"text":"I don't even have it for myself."},{"time":200000,"text":"I left San Francisco,\nwhere I live, on Monday,"},{"time":203000,"text":"and I was getting on the plane\nfor this conference."},{"time":205790,"text":"And my daughter, who's three,\nwhen I dropped her off at preschool,"},{"time":208910,"text":"did that whole hugging-the-leg, crying,\n\"Mommy, don't get on the plane\" thing."},{"time":212601,"text":"This is hard. I feel guilty sometimes."},{"time":215447,"text":"I know no women,"},{"time":217000,"text":"whether they're at home\nor whether they're in the workforce,"},{"time":219834,"text":"who don't feel that sometimes."},{"time":221397,"text":"So I'm not saying\nthat staying in the workforce"},{"time":224000,"text":"is the right thing for everyone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":226328,"text":"My talk today is about\nwhat the messages are"},{"time":229000,"text":"if you do want to stay in the workforce,"},{"time":231381,"text":"and I think there are three."},{"time":233515,"text":"One, sit at the table."},{"time":235904,"text":"Two, make your partner a real partner."},{"time":239206,"text":"And three, don't leave before you leave."},{"time":243796,"text":"Number one: sit at the table."},{"time":245854,"text":"Just a couple weeks ago at Facebook,"},{"time":247703,"text":"we hosted a very senior\ngovernment official,"},{"time":250000,"text":"and he came in to meet with senior execs"},{"time":253245,"text":"from around Silicon Valley."},{"time":255354,"text":"And everyone kind of sat at the table."},{"time":257560,"text":"He had these two women\nwho were traveling with him"},{"time":260156,"text":"pretty senior in his department,"},{"time":262000,"text":"and I kind of said to them,"},{"time":263310,"text":"\"Sit at the table.\nCome on, sit at the table,\""},{"time":265548,"text":"and they sat on the side of the room."},{"time":268533,"text":"When I was in college, my senior year,"},{"time":270509,"text":"I took a course called\nEuropean Intellectual History."},{"time":273032,"text":"Don't you love that kind\nof thing from college?"},{"time":275263,"text":"I wish I could do that now."},{"time":277000,"text":"And I took it with my roommate, Carrie,"},{"time":279000,"text":"who was then a brilliant\nliterary student --"},{"time":281564,"text":"and went on to be a brilliant\nliterary scholar --"},{"time":283898,"text":"and my brother -- smart guy,"},{"time":285939,"text":"but a water-polo-playing pre-med,"},{"time":287578,"text":"who was a sophomore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":289000,"text":"The three of us take this class together."},{"time":291558,"text":"And then Carrie reads all the books\nin the original Greek and Latin,"},{"time":295758,"text":"goes to all the lectures."},{"time":297474,"text":"I read all the books in English"},{"time":299548,"text":"and go to most of the lectures."},{"time":301229,"text":"My brother is kind of busy."},{"time":303000,"text":"He reads one book of 12\nand goes to a couple of lectures,"},{"time":306736,"text":"marches himself up to our room"},{"time":309807,"text":"a couple days before the exam\nto get himself tutored."},{"time":312857,"text":"The three of us go to the exam\ntogether, and we sit down."},{"time":315562,"text":"And we sit there for three hours --"},{"time":317745,"text":"and our little blue notebooks\n-- yes, I'm that old."},{"time":320150,"text":"We walk out, we look at each other,\nand we say, \"How did you do?\""},{"time":323389,"text":"And Carrie says, \"Boy, I feel like\nI didn't really draw out the main point"},{"time":326890,"text":"on the Hegelian dialectic.\""},{"time":328489,"text":"And I say, \"God, I really\nwish I had really connected"},{"time":331438,"text":"John Locke's theory of property\nwith the philosophers that follow.\""},{"time":334677,"text":"And my brother says,"},{"time":336205,"text":"\"I got the top grade in the class.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":338144,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":340113,"text":"\"You got the top grade in the class?"},{"time":342233,"text":"You don't know anything.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":343807,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":345231,"text":"The problem with these stories\nis that they show what the data shows:"},{"time":349803,"text":"women systematically\nunderestimate their own abilities."},{"time":353317,"text":"If you test men and women,"},{"time":355000,"text":"and you ask them questions\non totally objective criteria like GPAs,"},{"time":358618,"text":"men get it wrong slightly high,"},{"time":360506,"text":"and women get it wrong slightly low."},{"time":363000,"text":"Women do not negotiate\nfor themselves in the workforce."},{"time":366000,"text":"A study in the last two years"},{"time":368000,"text":"of people entering\nthe workforce out of college"},{"time":370641,"text":"showed that 57 percent\nof boys entering, or men, I guess,"},{"time":375000,"text":"are negotiating their first salary,"},{"time":377425,"text":"and only seven percent of women."},{"time":380137,"text":"And most importantly,"},{"time":382280,"text":"men attribute their success to themselves,"},{"time":385000,"text":"and women attribute it\nto other external factors."},{"time":388000,"text":"If you ask men why they did a good job,"},{"time":390397,"text":"they'll say, \"I'm awesome."},{"time":393000,"text":"Obviously. Why are you even asking?\""},{"time":396000,"text":"If you ask women why they did a good job,"},{"time":398000,"text":"what they'll say is someone helped them,"},{"time":400000,"text":"they got lucky, they worked really hard."},{"time":402646,"text":"Why does this matter?"},{"time":404000,"text":"Boy, it matters a lot."},{"time":406000,"text":"Because no one gets to the corner office"},{"time":409000,"text":"by sitting on the side, not at the table,"},{"time":411578,"text":"and no one gets the promotion"},{"time":413605,"text":"if they don't think\nthey deserve their success,"},{"time":416184,"text":"or they don't even understand\ntheir own success."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419852,"text":"I wish the answer were easy."},{"time":421640,"text":"I wish I could go tell\nall the young women I work for,"},{"time":424276,"text":"these fabulous women,"},{"time":425314,"text":"\"Believe in yourself\nand negotiate for yourself."},{"time":427588,"text":"Own your own success.\""},{"time":429366,"text":"I wish I could tell that to my daughter."},{"time":432000,"text":"But it's not that simple."},{"time":433912,"text":"Because what the data shows,\nabove all else, is one thing,"},{"time":437504,"text":"which is that success and likeability\nare positively correlated for men"},{"time":441829,"text":"and negatively correlated for women."},{"time":444621,"text":"And everyone's nodding,\nbecause we all know this to be true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":448212,"text":"There's a really good study\nthat shows this really well."},{"time":451000,"text":"There's a famous Harvard\nBusiness School study"},{"time":453215,"text":"on a woman named Heidi Roizen."},{"time":454872,"text":"And she's an operator\nin a company in Silicon Valley,"},{"time":459300,"text":"and she uses her contacts"},{"time":461000,"text":"to become a very successful\nventure capitalist."},{"time":464000,"text":"In 2002 -- not so long ago --"},{"time":466000,"text":"a professor who was then\nat Columbia University"},{"time":468263,"text":"took that case\nand made it [Howard] Roizen."},{"time":471000,"text":"And he gave the case out, both of them,\nto two groups of students."},{"time":474527,"text":"He changed exactly one word:"},{"time":477483,"text":"\"Heidi\" to \"Howard.\""},{"time":479000,"text":"But that one word made\na really big difference."},{"time":482547,"text":"He then surveyed the students,"},{"time":484202,"text":"and the good news was the students,\nboth men and women,"},{"time":486892,"text":"thought Heidi and Howard\nwere equally competent,"},{"time":489310,"text":"and that's good."},{"time":491000,"text":"The bad news was\nthat everyone liked Howard."},{"time":493707,"text":"He's a great guy.\nYou want to work for him."},{"time":495731,"text":"You want to spend the day\nfishing with him."},{"time":497755,"text":"But Heidi? Not so sure."},{"time":499341,"text":"She's a little out for herself.\nShe's a little political."},{"time":502230,"text":"You're not sure\nyou'd want to work for her."},{"time":505000,"text":"This is the complication."},{"time":507000,"text":"We have to tell our daughters\nand our colleagues,"},{"time":509334,"text":"we have to tell ourselves\nto believe we got the A,"},{"time":512042,"text":"to reach for the promotion,\nto sit at the table,"},{"time":515000,"text":"and we have to do it in a world"},{"time":516803,"text":"where, for them, there are sacrifices\nthey will make for that,"},{"time":520422,"text":"even though for their brothers,\nthere are not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":523817,"text":"The saddest thing about all of this\nis that it's really hard to remember this."},{"time":527508,"text":"And I'm about to tell a story\nwhich is truly embarrassing for me,"},{"time":530580,"text":"but I think important."},{"time":532270,"text":"I gave this talk at Facebook\nnot so long ago"},{"time":535491,"text":"to about 100 employees,"},{"time":538004,"text":"and a couple hours later,\nthere was a young woman who works there"},{"time":541076,"text":"sitting outside my little desk,\nand she wanted to talk to me."},{"time":544439,"text":"I said, okay, and she sat down,\nand we talked."},{"time":546606,"text":"And she said, \"I learned something today."},{"time":548583,"text":"I learned that I need to keep my hand up.\""},{"time":550979,"text":"\"What do you mean?\""},{"time":552035,"text":"She said, \"You're giving this talk,"},{"time":553853,"text":"and you said you would take\ntwo more questions."},{"time":556174,"text":"I had my hand up with many other people,"},{"time":558278,"text":"and you took two more questions."},{"time":559897,"text":"I put my hand down, and I noticed\nall the women did the same,"},{"time":562831,"text":"and then you took more questions,"},{"time":564784,"text":"only from the men.\""},{"time":567156,"text":"And I thought to myself,"},{"time":568471,"text":"\"Wow, if it's me -- who cares\nabout this, obviously --"},{"time":571300,"text":"giving this talk --"},{"time":573258,"text":"and during this talk, I can't even notice\nthat the men's hands are still raised,"},{"time":579000,"text":"and the women's hands are still raised,"},{"time":581000,"text":"how good are we"},{"time":582202,"text":"as managers of our companies\nand our organizations"},{"time":584930,"text":"at seeing that the men\nare reaching for opportunities"},{"time":587479,"text":"more than women?\""},{"time":589277,"text":"We've got to get women\nto sit at the table."}]},{"cues":[{"time":591691,"text":"(Cheers)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":592716,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":595948,"text":"Message number two:"},{"time":597295,"text":"Make your partner a real partner."},{"time":599206,"text":"I've become convinced that we've made\nmore progress in the workforce"},{"time":602421,"text":"than we have in the home."},{"time":604000,"text":"The data shows this very clearly."},{"time":607000,"text":"If a woman and a man\nwork full-time and have a child,"},{"time":611203,"text":"the woman does twice the amount\nof housework the man does,"},{"time":614580,"text":"and the woman does three times\nthe amount of childcare the man does."},{"time":619447,"text":"So she's got three jobs\nor two jobs, and he's got one."},{"time":623221,"text":"Who do you think drops out\nwhen someone needs to be home more?"},{"time":626814,"text":"The causes of this are really complicated,\nand I don't have time to go into them."},{"time":630648,"text":"And I don't think Sunday football-watching\nand general laziness is the cause."}]},{"cues":[{"time":634608,"text":"I think the cause is more complicated."},{"time":636846,"text":"I think, as a society,"},{"time":638359,"text":"we put more pressure\non our boys to succeed"},{"time":640600,"text":"than we do on our girls."},{"time":642454,"text":"I know men that stay home"},{"time":644506,"text":"and work in the home\nto support wives with careers,"},{"time":647597,"text":"and it's hard."},{"time":648648,"text":"When I go to the Mommy-and-Me stuff\nand I see the father there,"},{"time":652000,"text":"I notice that the other mommies\ndon't play with him."},{"time":656000,"text":"And that's a problem,"},{"time":658000,"text":"because we have to make it\nas important a job,"},{"time":661210,"text":"because it's the hardest job\nin the world to work inside the home,"},{"time":664613,"text":"for people of both genders,"},{"time":666117,"text":"if we're going to even things out and let\nwomen stay in the workforce."}]},{"cues":[{"time":669635,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":671000,"text":"Studies show that households\nwith equal earning"},{"time":673263,"text":"and equal responsibility"},{"time":675229,"text":"also have half the divorce rate."},{"time":677414,"text":"And if that wasn't good enough motivation\nfor everyone out there,"},{"time":680622,"text":"they also have more --"},{"time":682459,"text":"how shall I say this on this stage?"},{"time":684293,"text":"They know each other more\nin the biblical sense as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":687000,"text":"(Cheers)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":689517,"text":"Message number three:"},{"time":691476,"text":"Don't leave before you leave."},{"time":693539,"text":"I think there's a really deep irony"},{"time":695306,"text":"to the fact that actions\nwomen are taking --"},{"time":697415,"text":"and I see this all the time --"},{"time":699000,"text":"with the objective\nof staying in the workforce"},{"time":702150,"text":"actually lead to their eventually leaving."},{"time":704739,"text":"Here's what happens:"},{"time":706000,"text":"We're all busy. Everyone's busy.\nA woman's busy."},{"time":708568,"text":"And she starts thinking\nabout having a child,"},{"time":711000,"text":"and from the moment she starts\nthinking about having a child,"},{"time":714000,"text":"she starts thinking\nabout making room for that child."},{"time":716997,"text":"\"How am I going to fit this\ninto everything else I'm doing?\""},{"time":720182,"text":"And literally from that moment,"},{"time":722856,"text":"she doesn't raise her hand anymore,"},{"time":725174,"text":"she doesn't look for a promotion,\nshe doesn't take on the new project,"},{"time":728528,"text":"she doesn't say, \"Me. I want to do that.\""},{"time":730529,"text":"She starts leaning back."},{"time":732202,"text":"The problem is that --"},{"time":733623,"text":"let's say she got pregnant\nthat day, that day --"},{"time":737211,"text":"nine months of pregnancy,\nthree months of maternity leave,"},{"time":740000,"text":"six months to catch your breath --"},{"time":742174,"text":"Fast-forward two years,"},{"time":743660,"text":"more often -- and as I've seen it --"},{"time":745644,"text":"women start thinking\nabout this way earlier --"},{"time":748182,"text":"when they get engaged, or married,"},{"time":750096,"text":"when they start thinking\nabout having a child,"},{"time":752268,"text":"which can take a long time."},{"time":753759,"text":"One woman came to see me about this."},{"time":755791,"text":"She looked a little young."},{"time":757544,"text":"And I said, \"So are you and your husband\nthinking about having a baby?\""},{"time":760902,"text":"And she said, \"Oh no, I'm not married.\""},{"time":762888,"text":"She didn't even have a boyfriend."}]},{"cues":[{"time":764487,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":765512,"text":"I said, \"You're thinking about this\njust way too early.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":769219,"text":"But the point is that what happens"},{"time":771861,"text":"once you start\nkind of quietly leaning back?"},{"time":775543,"text":"Everyone who's been through this --"},{"time":777333,"text":"and I'm here to tell you,\nonce you have a child at home,"},{"time":780100,"text":"your job better be really good to go back,"},{"time":782710,"text":"because it's hard to leave\nthat kid at home."},{"time":784877,"text":"Your job needs to be challenging."},{"time":786765,"text":"It needs to be rewarding."},{"time":788455,"text":"You need to feel like you're\nmaking a difference."},{"time":791000,"text":"And if two years ago\nyou didn't take a promotion"},{"time":794000,"text":"and some guy next to you did,"},{"time":796290,"text":"if three years ago you stopped\nlooking for new opportunities,"},{"time":800000,"text":"you're going to be bored"},{"time":801752,"text":"because you should have kept\nyour foot on the gas pedal."},{"time":805212,"text":"Don't leave before you leave."},{"time":807631,"text":"Stay in."},{"time":809000,"text":"Keep your foot on the gas pedal,"},{"time":811000,"text":"until the very day you need to leave\nto take a break for a child --"},{"time":815655,"text":"and then make your decisions."},{"time":817896,"text":"Don't make decisions too far in advance,"},{"time":820398,"text":"particularly ones you're not\neven conscious you're making."}]},{"cues":[{"time":824511,"text":"My generation really, sadly,"},{"time":826276,"text":"is not going to change\nthe numbers at the top."},{"time":828571,"text":"They're just not moving."},{"time":830315,"text":"We are not going to get\nto where 50 percent of the population --"},{"time":833541,"text":"in my generation, there will not\nbe 50 percent of [women]"},{"time":836232,"text":"at the top of any industry."},{"time":838870,"text":"But I'm hopeful that future\ngenerations can."},{"time":842284,"text":"I think a world where half\nof our countries and our companies"},{"time":846997,"text":"were run by women,\nwould be a better world."},{"time":849434,"text":"It's not just because people would know\nwhere the women's bathrooms are,"},{"time":852839,"text":"even though that would be very helpful."},{"time":855516,"text":"I think it would be a better world."},{"time":858243,"text":"I have two children."},{"time":859542,"text":"I have a five-year-old son\nand a two-year-old daughter."},{"time":862560,"text":"I want my son to have a choice"},{"time":864261,"text":"to contribute fully\nin the workforce or at home,"},{"time":867357,"text":"and I want my daughter\nto have the choice to not just succeed,"},{"time":871277,"text":"but to be liked for her accomplishments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":874000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":875134,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}